{{Infobox war faction | name = KNU/KNLA Peace Council | native_name = | native_name_lang = my | war = [[Karen conflict]] | image = [[File:Logo of the KNU-KNLA Peace Council.png|175px]] | caption = | active = 31 January 2007 – present | ideology = [[Karen people|Karen]] [[nationalism]] | leaders = Maj. Gen. Saw Htay Maung | clans = | headquarters = [[To-kawko]], [[Kayin State]]. [[Myanmar]] | area = <200 | strength = | partof = | previous = {{flagicon image|Flag of the Karen National Union.svg}} [[Karen National Union]] * {{flagicon image|Karen National Liberation Army flag.svg}} 7th brigade of the [[Karen National Liberation Army]] | next = | split = | allies = {{flag|Myanmar}} | opponents = | battles = | website = }}
The '''KNU/KNLA Peace Council''' ([[Abbreviation|abbreviated]] '''KPC''') is an armed opposition group in [[Myanmar]] (Burma).<ref>{{cite news|title=Karen Rebel Group Defies Myanmar Military Order to Disarm|url=http://www.rfa.org/english/news/myanmar/karen-09172014175131.html|accessdate=8 January 2018|work=Radio Free Asia|language=en}}</ref> It was founded on 31 January 2007 by [[Major General]] Saw Htay Maung, the then-commander of the 7th Brigade of the [[Karen National Liberation Army]] (KNLA). Despite its name, it is not part of or sponsored by its former parent organisation, the [[Karen National Union]] (KNU), nor the KNLA.<ref>{{cite web|title=Burma Partnership » KNU/KNLA Peace Council|url=http://www.burmapartnership.org/tag/knuknla-peace-council/|website=www.burmapartnership.org|accessdate=15 October 2017}}</ref> The group is a signatory of the [[Nationwide Ceasefire Agreement]], which was finalised in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=KPC|url=http://www.mmpeacemonitor.org/background/economic-and-political-stakes/162-kpc|website=www.mmpeacemonitor.org|accessdate=15 October 2017|language=en-gb}}</ref>
