'''Leontiy Ivanovich Sivstov''' (1872-1919) was a church reader who lived in [[Unalaska]]. Along with [[Aleksey Yachmenev]], who like Sivstov was Aleut himself, Sivstov accompanied [[Waldemar Jochelson]] on his 1909-1910 ethnological studies on the Aleut.

==References==
* [[Knut Bergsland|Bergsland, Knut]] (1994). Aleut Dictionary = Unangam Tunudgusii: an unabridged lexicon of the Aleutian, Pribilof, and Commander Islands Aleut language. Fairbanks, AK: Alaska Native Language Center, University of Alaska. {{ISBN|1-55500-047-9}}. pg. viii

