{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox musical artist |name = Maggie Ferguson |background = non_vocal_instrumentalist |image = |caption = |origin = [[Sydney]], Australia |genre = [[Tango music|Tango]] |occupation = musician |years_active = 1996 – present |label = |associated_acts = |website = [http://www.facebook.com/pages/edit/?id=281798418665#!/pages/Tango-Music-Australia/281798418665] }}
'''Maggie Ferguson''' (born in Sydney) is an [[Australia]]n violinist and bandoneonista who studied orchestral tango at Orquesta Escuela de Tango Emilio Balcarce in Buenos Aires from 2003. In 2009, with the [[Sydney Youth Orchestra]]s Association (SYO), she created Tango Oz, Australia's first national tango orchestra which she directs from the bandoneon. TangoOz were the focus of Sydney's first Tango Escuela held by the SYO in collaboration with the Conservatorium High School in July 2009 under the guest direction of [[Ignacio Varchausky]] and [[Santiago Polimeni]]. A second collaboration with Canberra Youth Music occurred in 2010 for Resonate Festival, including [[William Barton (musician)|William Barton]], [[Ignacio Varchausky]] and [[Santiago Polimeni]]. This showcased the traditional Argentine tango instrument, [[bandoneon]] performed with improvised [[didgeridoo]].
==Discography== * [http://tangomusicproject.com/ Tango Project Loco Bohemia 2012], recorded in Buenos Aires.
