'''Percy Cooke Bishop''' (1869 – 1961) was a British journalist and [[philatelist]] who proposed what became the [[Roll of Distinguished Philatelists]]. He was appointed to the Roll in 1921.<ref>''[http://www.abps.org.uk/Awards/Roll_of_Distinguished_Philatelists/RDP_Background_20111231_LR.pdf Background notes on The Roll of Distinguished Philatelists September 2011]'', Roll of Distinguished Philatelists Trust, London, 2011. [https://www.webcitation.org/6OlHSBOTl Archived here.]</ref><ref name=abps>[http://www.abps.org.uk/Home/Who_Was_Who/index.xalter#B Who Was Who in British Philately], [[Association of British Philatelic Societies]], 2014. Retrieved 1 May 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/5zDx9UBpl Archived here.]</ref>

